<br>
dude...that statement is so very, very, very wrong...I dont even know where to begin...<br>
<br>
...other than to say, the stimulus the brain gets from physical drugs can be re-created by a mental situation. After all, it comes down to the stimuli that your brain recieves that is addicting... in mental, physical, emotional, and social behavorial addictions. <br>
<br>
There are many books on the subject.<br>
<br>
is smoking a habit...or an addiction?<br>
<br>
does someone who chews their nails constantly and dont realize they are doing it (even when told to stop) have a habit....or a mental addiction?<br>
<br>
does someone who is obsessed with things having to be absolutley clean have a habit..........or a mental and/or social addiction?<br>
<br>
or is a habit..... really a  lesser form of an addiction?<br>
